task.summary: Now we have three packages. GUI is separated into a specific package. However the code for the GUI's can still be condensed further. I have also created a third package for test classes in which I have generated several test classes. The test classes are just skeleton code so far but will be easy to populate with conditions once we're done . Shane out *mic drop*

Shane: Did a lot of refactoring. Deleted all the product class files (Copy.java, Envelope.java, Folder.java, Paper.java, PaperClip.java, Pen.java, Pencil.java and Ruler.java) and replaced them with one concrete product class as they were all doing the exact same thing. Refactored productFactory also to cut code in half using the new concrete product and an enhanced for loop.

Shane: Deleted user.java & staff.java due to the fact they were completely useless and did nothing. I created a concrete user class but I have not yet implemented it as there seems to be a problem registering users to the database
Shane: Deleted Logistics , Warehouse and Manager class
